verbose_text: Although carrying the G allele or G/G genotype was reportedly associated with lower HDL-C levels [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], we found no association between the A-3826G polymorphism and HDL-C levels [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] as well as a possibly protective association of the G/G genotype with low HDL-cholesterolemia [XREF_BIBR].
